    duration: "63.0",
    updated_at: "2014-04-25T19:03:43.463Z",
    name: "Drifting with only one hand on the steering wheel is no problem for this guy",
    long_name: null,
    description: "###*Is this video Holy? Rank it.* Drifting takes two hands, there is no doubt about that. Shifting and pulling the e-brake require your right hand (or left if you're weird on drive on the other side of the road). Steering requires your left hand. And even a professional like Chris Forsberg will [put his right hand on the steering wheel][1] going through a hard turn. It's just the nature of it, and putting both hands on the wheel at times are completely necessary. Not so for Niculae Dobre though. Dobre is from Romania and clearly an underground badass. During this entire tandem with a fellow drifter Dobre does not once put his right hand on the wheel. Taking these hard turns with only one hand is unfathomable, and we're still scratching our heads as to how he does this in his V-8 BMW E30. ###*Have you ever seen anyone else drift with only one hand on the steering wheel? Tell us in the Comments.* [1]: http://www.networka.com/videos/28428/drift-with-chris-forsberg-at-formula-drift-long-beach",
    short_description: "His name is Niculae Dobre",
    meta_description: "Romanian drifter Niculae Dobre can drift during tandem with only one hand on the steering wheel. He might be the maddest of them all.",
    meta_title: "Drifter Niculae Dobre only uses one hand to drift",
    original: null,
    status: "published",
    uploaded_at: "2014-03-17T21:07:03.000Z",
